IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: To relieve human suffering by facilitating the donation retrieval processing and equitable distribution of corneal and other human cadaveric tissue for transplantation research education and other medical needs worldwide
IRS990.MissionDescription: To relieve human suffering by facilitating the donation retrieval processing and equitable distribution of corneal and other human cadaveric tissue for transplantation research education and other medical needs worldwide
IRS990.Description: Medical Services of Eye and Tissue Banking including the recovery processing analysis testing and distribution of donated cadaveric tissues primarily for transplantation but also for medical researcheducation and publiccommunity educational p rograms The organization also supports and manages the activities of six additional eye and tissue banking organizationsall are 501c3 entities Individuals served with tissues used for transplantation or surgical implantation estimates - Mu sculoskeletalskin and other tissues made available to patients - 100000 - Corneas made available to patients through distribution system - 7000

Activity2.Description: Public Health Education - eye and tissue donor outreach and donor advocacy

Activity3.Description: International Outreach - providing expertise and services to advance eye and tissue banking worldwide

ActivityOther.Description: Research - providing tissues for medical research Tissue Banks International donates tissues for transplants research and teaching for which processing costs are incurred sometimes nominal reimbursement is received for these services

IRS990ScheduleA.FactsAndCircumstancesTest: Type of supporting organization Part I Lines 11a - 11d The Form 990 is prepared and reviewed by the senior financial employees of the organization

Form990ScheduleFPartIV.Explanation: Part III-Gratis Tissue - The organization distributes a significant number of its transplantable tissue recovered in the US to patients in need overseas The expenditures for the recovery of these tissues is generally incurred in the United States For these tissues recovered in the US and distributed outside the US the eyetissue banking organization first makes available tissue to those in need in its service area and the United States If tissue is not needed in the US it is offered for use for patients outside the US The eyetissue banking organization made available numerous corneas for free gratis or at reduced fees for transplantation in patients who are indigent or with reduced economic means The organization makes available Gratis tissues free of charge to many around the world In fiscal year 2009-10 there was a particular need in the region Middle East and North Africa where most of the gratis tissues were distributed Part I Line 3 Column F Total expenditures in region The organization does not account for expenses by region The total expenses for the International Program of 614405 are allocated based on the estimated percentage of the work dedicated to the specific region

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Identifier: 01 No written policy information Part I line 1b
Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: The Box checked Housing allowance or residence for personal use - An individual listed in Part II was instructed to work out of a different office a different region of the US and during the transition period the management of the organization agreed to reimburse certain temporary housing and travel related expenses The Box checked Tax indemnification and gross up payment - For this same individual noted above these reimbursements for housing and travel were considered as ordinary compensation to the individual and so the organization also agreed to pay the personal income taxes incurred by the individual who received these reimbursements

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Identifier: 02 Listed persons compensation information Part I line 4
Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: VP of Marketing did receive severence pay in the period covered by this return

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Identifier: 03 Compensation contingent on revenues Part I line 5
Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: There is an individual listed in Part II who receives compensation which is partly linked to revenues The individual holds the position of Vice President of Distribution of servicesallografts made available to hospitals and surgeons and a portion of his total compensation is based on certain revenue amounts being reached

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Identifier: 04 Other non-fixed payments Part I line 7
Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: Key employees officers and senior managers are eligible for monetary bonuses based on performance relative to the organizational mission Eligibility is typically linked to the organizations annual performance appraisal system Disbursements are included in the individuals W-2 compensation reported in Part II

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 01. Form 990 governing body review (Part VI, line 11)
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: No documents are supplied to the entire Board for review

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 02. Conflict of interest policy compliance (Part VI, line 12c)
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Senior management of the organization and directors complete and sign a Conflict of Interest disclosure statement Potential conflicts of directors are identified and disclosed in the audited financial statements of the organization Directors are expected to excuse themselves from participation in any decisionvote in which they have a financial or other independent interest Senior managers and all employees are expected to disclose to their supervisor any potential conflicts they may have in their employment or other organizational related activities Senior management monitors activities in an effort to identify potential conflicts using an open door policy that encourages the flow of information from employees concerned with conflicts that may exist

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 03. CEO, executive director, top management comp (Part VI, line 15a)
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: A Compensation Committee comprised of members of the Board of Directors determines that the PresidentCEOs salary is appropriate and reasonable in relation to comparable positions in similar organizations In addition the PresidentCEO is formally appraised on his performance on an annual basis and from this appraisal process the Chairman of the Board of Directors in consultation with other Board members determines the appropriate merit increase or bonus

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 04. Other officer or key employee compensation (Part VI, line 15b
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Management determines the appropriate salary ranges and pay grade for senior managers and all employees on a consistent basis using comparisons with comparable pay levels of similar organizationsfor similar comparable positions The company policy is to conduct annual written appraisals with all paid staff Merit increases bonuses and changes in compensation levels are linked to and justified by this formal appraisal process

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 05. Governing documents, etc, available to public (Part VI, line 19)
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Each year the organization provides an Annual Report on activities achievements and services provided which also includes a summary statement of activitiesrevenues and expenses There is not a formal policy with respect to disclosing governing documents policies and detailed financial information
